  "text": "Our previous research [CITATION_1] had found out that distribution of P retention in CWs with wetland plants was different in rhizosphere from that in non-rhizosphere areas compared to the system without plants. However, for the complete understanding of the spatial distribution of P retention in substrate of CWs, affecting factors like type and inflow hydraulic loading needed to be taken into account. Therefore, The purpose of this work was to verify the spatial variation of TP and inorganic P(Ca-P, Fe-P and Al-P) retention capacity in HSSF CWs and VSSF CWs under high and low hydraulic loading.",
